If this is called from the UI thread (accessed from the implementation of in the , then this service will make the GUI appear busy, as the UI thread is about to be blocked. This service will undo its changes, thus making the GUI appear normal and responsive, once the UI thread becomes idle.
Therefore, this method only needs to be called once per UI thread block, rather than once per long-running operation. In fact, the service will ignore additional calls if the UI thread has not gone idle since the first call was made.
